32:42.690 --> 32:49.800
Here's the definition of the
quantum Fourier transform when the dimension is an
arbitrary positive integer N.

306
32:49.800 --> 32:57.570
Here we're thinking about this operation as being an operation on a system whose classical states are
zero up to N minus one.

307
32:57.570 --> 33:04.980
And here the matrix that
describes this operation has been expressed using
the direct notation.

308
33:04.980 --> 33:14.190
We can also describe it in terms of its action
on standard basis states, just to connect it with
