322
34:35.610 --> 34:40.950
And that is to define a
complex number omega N, like we have here.

323
34:40.950 --> 34:47.500
Specifically as e to the two pi I over N, which can also be written
using signs and cosines

324
34:47.500 --> 34:56.910
as we have right here. Sometimes we call this
number an N through of unity because when we raise it
to the power N, we get one.

325
34:56.910 --> 35:00.330
Here's a figure that shows a few examples.

326
35:00.330 --> 35:08.160
Omega one is equal to one, omega two is equal to negative one, and omega four is equal to I.

327
35:08.160 --> 35:17.010
In general to get omega N, we can imagine slicing up the unit circle into N equal size pieces like it's a pizza being shared by N people

328
35:17.010 --> 35:23.220
and omega N is at the
corner of the first piece, assuming that the other corner
of that piece is at one.

329
35:23.220 --> 35:32.430
So in particular as N
gets larger and larger, the pieces will get smaller and smaller, and omega N will get
closer and closer to one.

330
35:32.430 --> 35:38.970
And now if we use that notation we can express the
